ALEXIS: Not bad.

00:00:15.770 --> 00:00:19.300
So we're here today to
talk about extensions

00:00:19.300 --> 00:00:21.140
versus Chrome applications.

00:00:21.140 --> 00:00:24.190
There are subtle or
important differences

00:00:24.190 --> 00:00:26.200
that we think you
should be aware of.

00:00:26.200 --> 00:00:28.960
And Francois will
help you and me

00:00:28.960 --> 00:00:30.740
understand what those
differences are.

00:00:30.740 --> 00:00:33.490
So Francois, let's start
probably with extensions.

00:00:33.490 --> 00:00:35.990
They were the ones that
were the first ones around.

00:00:35.990 --> 00:00:37.540
And as the name
implies, they were

00:00:37.540 --> 00:00:38.785
extensions to the browsers.

00:00:38.785 --> 00:00:39.410
FRANCOIS: Yeah.

00:00:39.410 --> 00:00:41.420
ALEXIS: Tell us more about
what they really are.

00:00:41.420 --> 00:00:44.010
FRANCOIS: So
basically, extensions

00:00:44.010 --> 00:00:47.610
extend functionality
for the Chrome browser.

00:00:47.610 --> 00:00:51.500
They have no UI
at all, actually.

00:00:51.500 --> 00:00:57.740
For instance, let's take
this Gmail extension,

00:00:57.740 --> 00:00:59.340
which is the browser action.

00:00:59.340 --> 00:01:00.650
You can see it all the time.

00:01:00.650 --> 00:01:03.640
ALEXIS: It's associated with
the browser instance itself.

00:01:03.640 --> 00:01:05.056
FRANCOIS: Next to
the Chrome menu.

00:01:05.056 --> 00:01:06.740
ALEXIS: Not for a given page.

00:01:06.740 --> 00:01:10.180
FRANCOIS: Next one
is the RSS extension.

00:01:10.180 --> 00:01:10.950
Pretty simple.

00:01:10.950 --> 00:01:15.460
you will see this icon only when
the web page has an RSS feed.

00:01:15.460 --> 00:01:16.640
ALEXIS: OK.

00:01:16.640 --> 00:01:20.199
FRANCOIS: And so this is
a kind of UI you can get,

00:01:20.199 --> 00:01:21.740
or sometimes you
don't have anything.

00:01:21.740 --> 00:01:23.557
Like for instance, AdBlock.

00:01:23.557 --> 00:01:24.140
ALEXIS: Right.

00:01:24.140 --> 00:01:25.556
FRANCOIS: It works
under the hood,

00:01:25.556 --> 00:01:29.270
and gets all the
requests, and filters out

00:01:29.270 --> 00:01:30.887
all the ads, for instance.

00:01:30.887 --> 00:01:31.470
ALEXIS: Right.

00:01:31.470 --> 00:01:34.690
So I suppose here, what
you want is something

00:01:34.690 --> 00:01:36.680
that extends the
functionality of a browser,

00:01:36.680 --> 00:01:39.210
but is not a full
fledged application.

00:01:39.210 --> 00:01:41.740
If you want to do a full
fledged application,

00:01:41.740 --> 00:01:43.570
there at these two
types of applications

00:01:43.570 --> 00:01:45.140
that people can consider.

00:01:45.140 --> 00:01:48.050
The first one is called
hosted applications.

00:01:48.050 --> 00:01:50.480
So these are just
typical websites,

00:01:50.480 --> 00:01:52.150
but with a little
bit of metadata.

00:01:52.150 --> 00:01:53.700
Tell us more about what this is.

00:01:53.700 --> 00:01:54.340
FRANCOIS: Yeah.

00:01:54.340 --> 00:01:56.260
A hosted app is a
regular web page,

00:01:56.260 --> 00:02:00.260
so it works online,
plus some metadata,

00:02:00.260 --> 00:02:02.570
like some permissions
that have been

00:02:02.570 --> 00:02:04.690
granted to the application.

00:02:04.690 --> 00:02:07.226
So let's take, for
instance, Google Drive.

00:02:07.226 --> 00:02:10.370
Google Drive is a perfect
example of a nice hosted app.

00:02:10.370 --> 00:02:14.440
It has the storage permission,
the notification permission,

00:02:14.440 --> 00:02:15.960
the clipboard permission.

00:02:15.960 --> 00:02:19.080
And basically, once
you know you've

00:02:19.080 --> 00:02:20.860
got this permission
for free, you

00:02:20.860 --> 00:02:22.340
won't be prompted
by Chrome, OK, do

00:02:22.340 --> 00:02:23.830
you want to, blah, blah, blah.

00:02:23.830 --> 00:02:26.420
ALEXIS: But as a user, I develop
the application just once.

00:02:26.420 --> 00:02:29.200
The experience of the user
is a little bit different,

00:02:29.200 --> 00:02:31.020
in the sense that
the user is not

00:02:31.020 --> 00:02:33.710
prompted every time for
the specific permissions

00:02:33.710 --> 00:02:36.270
if it's a hosted application.

00:02:36.270 --> 00:02:40.580
So as you said, this is
for online applications.

00:02:40.580 --> 00:02:44.390
So clearly a hosted application
lives in the browser

00:02:44.390 --> 00:02:45.660
and works online.

00:02:45.660 --> 00:02:51.030
Which brings us to the third
type of extension in general.

00:02:51.030 --> 00:02:55.530
But those are packaged
extensions, or Chrome apps.

00:02:55.530 --> 00:02:59.046
One thing that makes them
different from the others

00:02:59.046 --> 00:03:00.420
is the fact that
they're offline.

00:03:00.420 --> 00:03:01.378
But there's more to it.

00:03:01.378 --> 00:03:02.380
Tell us more.

00:03:02.380 --> 00:03:04.060
FRANCOIS: So those
are my favorite,

00:03:04.060 --> 00:03:07.370
and they deserve more
than two minutes for sure.

00:03:07.370 --> 00:03:10.379
We'll do another video, I hope,
if you let me do one, please.

00:03:10.379 --> 00:03:10.920
ALEXIS: Sure.

00:03:10.920 --> 00:03:14.000
FRANCOIS: OK, so in a
nutshell, a Chrome packaged app

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:20.550
is a native application, built
with web technology, HTML5,

00:03:20.550 --> 00:03:24.150
CSS feed, JavaScript.

00:03:24.150 --> 00:03:27.140
It has a very, very strong
content security policy.

00:03:27.140 --> 00:03:31.500
If you don't know what is a CSP,
please Google Mike West CSP,

00:03:31.500 --> 00:03:34.040
and you will find tons of
YouTube videos for that.

00:03:34.040 --> 00:03:35.710
That's really
important if you are

00:03:35.710 --> 00:03:37.900
running a website right now.

00:03:37.900 --> 00:03:40.020
You need to implement a CSP.

00:03:40.020 --> 00:03:42.187
ALEXIS: So web sites
included, right?

00:03:42.187 --> 00:03:42.770
FRANCOIS: Yes.

00:03:42.770 --> 00:03:45.180
ALEXIS: This is not specific
to Chrome apps, extensions,

00:03:45.180 --> 00:03:47.220
this is web.

00:03:47.220 --> 00:03:49.380
And it's really something
you should look into.

00:03:49.380 --> 00:03:52.320
FRANCOIS: So CSP,
very strong CSP.

00:03:52.320 --> 00:03:56.040
And also you know they're
working offline, which

00:03:56.040 --> 00:03:59.320
is very important, which means
when you download and install

00:03:59.320 --> 00:04:02.520
a Chrome packaged app, it
comes with all the assets.

00:04:02.520 --> 00:04:04.980
CSS, JavaScript, images,
blah, blah, blah.

00:04:04.980 --> 00:04:09.720
And then, my favorite feature,
even though the web is great,

00:04:09.720 --> 00:04:12.450
there is still some
stuff we can't do,

00:04:12.450 --> 00:04:15.410
and that's why we
have the Chrome APIs.

00:04:15.410 --> 00:04:19.370
And with those APIs, we
can access hardware devices

00:04:19.370 --> 00:04:21.440
with USB, Bluetooth.

00:04:21.440 --> 00:04:25.150
We can also play with
sockets, like raw sockets.

00:04:25.150 --> 00:04:26.655
It's really, really cool.

00:04:29.410 --> 00:04:30.989
Yeah, we need to talk--

00:04:30.989 --> 00:04:32.780
ALEXIS: Yeah, we'll
