about this in another episode.

00:04:39.180 --> 00:04:40.710
What all of these
have in common,

00:04:40.710 --> 00:04:43.630
so extensions and both
types of applications,

00:04:43.630 --> 00:04:46.670
is that they're written in
the same set of technologies,

00:04:46.670 --> 00:04:48.860
as you said, HTML5.

00:04:48.860 --> 00:04:53.750
Tell us more about the
way you can develop them,

00:04:53.750 --> 00:04:56.090
deploy them, package them.

00:04:56.090 --> 00:04:59.177
Is it the same for
all of those as well?

00:04:59.177 --> 00:05:01.260
FRANCOIS: For Chrome
packaged apps and extensions,

00:05:01.260 --> 00:05:02.220
it's pretty easy.

00:05:02.220 --> 00:05:04.380
If you have Chrome,
you have all the tools

00:05:04.380 --> 00:05:07.100
you need to start creating one.

00:05:07.100 --> 00:05:10.740
You just go to Chrome colon
slash slash extension,

00:05:10.740 --> 00:05:12.420
and you check the
Developer Mode.

00:05:12.420 --> 00:05:14.407
We actually showed that
in the previous video.

00:05:14.407 --> 00:05:15.740
ALEXIS: The previous video, yes.

00:05:15.740 --> 00:05:17.690
FRANCOIS: You click on the
Load Unpacked Extension.

00:05:17.690 --> 00:05:19.648
You select your folder,
and bang, here you are.

00:05:19.648 --> 00:05:23.265
You can start to debug and
develop your real extension

00:05:23.265 --> 00:05:25.610
or application.

00:05:25.610 --> 00:05:28.650
And if you want to deploy
it now, it's pretty easy.

00:05:28.650 --> 00:05:32.300
You just zip it, upload it
to the Chrome Web Store,

00:05:32.300 --> 00:05:35.680
